{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: observation-medical-test-result-eu_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    A FRAME TEMPLATE that generates a FSH Observation instance conforming to
    the MedicalTestResultEuCore profile. It handles the instance header and
    category selection, then delegates all remaining body rules (id, code,
    value, reference range, narrative, etc.) to the shared partial:

      {% include 'observation-medical-test-body.fsh.twig' %}

    The %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% section markers, as well as the narrative
    (`text.div`) and all HTML bag operations, are provided by the included
    partial — this frame contributes only the FSH instance header and the
    category/performer block.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: MedicalTestResultEuCore

  CATEGORY SELECTION — BOOLEAN FLAG BRANCHING
    The observation category and performer are determined by three boolean
    flags passed from the PHP caller. The flags are mutually exclusive:

    ┌─────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Flag            │ Category slice and performer display                     │
    ├─────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ isVitaLSignCode │ category[VSCat].coding = vital-signs                    │
    │                 │ performer: "The Central European Examiners"             │
    │ isImagingCode   │ category.coding = imaging                               │
    │                 │ performer: "The Central European Radiology"             │
    │ isLaboratory    │ category[laboratory].coding = laboratory                │
    │                 │ performer: "The Central European Laboratory"            │
    │ (else / default)│ category.coding = laboratory (same as isLaboratory)    │
    │                 │ performer: "The Central European Laboratory"            │
    └─────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

    Named category slices:
      [VSCat]       — vital signs slice name (matches HL7 vitalsigns profile)
      [laboratory]  — laboratory slice name (matches EU lab profile)
    Imaging uses no named slice (plain `category.coding`).

  PERFORMER — PLACEHOLDER DISPLAY STRINGS
    All four branches emit a hardcoded `performer[+].display` string. A
    commented-out `performer[=]` reference line (to a fixed UUID) is present
    in each branch — retained for future use when real performer resources
    are available:
      { # * performer[=] = Reference(urn:uuid:e512e2e2-...) # }

  INCLUDE PATTERN
    The `{% include %}` statement passes the current Twig variable context
    automatically — all variables available in this frame (instanceid,
    labresult.*, etc.) are accessible inside the included partial without
    explicit `with` passing.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable         │ Type     │ Description                                      │
  ├──────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid       │ string   │ Resource id; passed to setInstance() here and    │
  │                  │          │ used as * id in the included partial.            │
  │ isVitaLSignCode  │ bool     │ True when the observation code is a vital sign.  │
  │ isImagingCode    │ bool     │ True when the observation code is an imaging     │
  │                  │          │ study result.                                    │
  │ isLaboratory     │ bool     │ True when the observation is a lab result.       │
  │ labresult.*      │ various  │ All labresult fields — passed through to the     │
  │                  │          │ included partial. See observation-medical-test-  │
  │                  │          │ body_fsh.twig for the full variable contract.    │
  └──────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED (category)
    $observation-category — http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/observation-category
      Codes: vital-signs, imaging, laboratory

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2026-03-01
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Observation-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicalTestResultEuCore
Title: "Medical Test Results"
Description: "Medical Test Results"
Usage: #inline

{#
  ── Category and performer selection ───────────────────────────────────────
  Mutually exclusive boolean flags determine the observation category slice
  and the hardcoded performer display string.

  Note on performer references: the commented-out performer[=] Reference lines
  contain a fixed placeholder UUID and are retained for when real performer
  resources are wired into the pipeline.
#}
{% if isVitaLSignCode %}
{# Vital sign: named [VSCat] slice; examiner performer #}
* category[VSCat].coding = $observation-category#vital-signs
* performer[+].display = "The Central European Examiners"
{# * performer[=] = Reference(urn:uuid:e512e2e2-9600-4c69-a269-af3ab5421e09) #}

{% elseif isImagingCode %}
{# Imaging: no named slice; radiology performer #}
* category.coding = $observation-category#imaging
* performer[+].display = "The Central European Radiology"
{# * performer[=] = Reference(urn:uuid:e512e2e2-9600-4c69-a269-af3ab5421e09) #}

{% elseif isLaboratory %}
{# Laboratory: named [laboratory] slice; lab performer #}
* category[laboratory].coding = $observation-category#laboratory
* performer[+].display = "The Central European Laboratory"
{# * performer[=] = Reference(urn:uuid:e512e2e2-9600-4c69-a269-af3ab5421e09) #}

{% else %}
{# Default — same as laboratory branch when no flag is set #}
* category.coding = $observation-category#laboratory
* performer[+].display = "The Central European Laboratory"
{# * performer[=] = Reference(urn:uuid:e512e2e2-9600-4c69-a269-af3ab5421e09) #}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Include shared observation body ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Delegates all remaining FSH rules (id, code, effectiveDateTime, value,
  referenceRange, bodySite, specimen, text.div) and all HTML bag operations
  to the shared partial. The %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% section markers are also
  provided by the partial.
#}
{% include 'observation-medical-test-body.fsh.twig' %}
